"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 17 "Note the effect  " }{TEXT 268 6 "ex
pand" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 269 8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 43 "  have
 on the way the calculation appears. " }{TEXT 306 223 "In the first li
ne it simply puts the problems ( but it will do the add and subtract p
arts of the problems).  The second line does the multiplication and di
vision part of the problems.  The third line simplfies the problems." 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The Map
le commands " }{TEXT 266 16 "expand, simplify" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }
{TEXT 267 6 "normal" }{TEXT -1 483 " can be use to rearrange, manipula
te and simplify (cancel common factors) algebraic sums, products and q
uotients of rational expressions.   When a rational expression is norm
alized, any common factors are cancelled.  Go back to each of your cal
culations of e., f., g., h. and i. and add to each line a command to e
xpand the calculation, to normalize the calculation, to simplify the c
alculation and both expand and normalize the calculation.  E.g., the l
ine for e. would change from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "F*H/G;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 2 "to" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 99 "F*H/G; exp
and(F*H/G); normal(F*H/G); simplify(F*H/G); expand(normal(F*H/G)); nor
mal(expand(F*H/G));" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 104 "(F/H)/G;expand((F/H)/G);normal((F/H)/G);
simplify((F/H)/G);expand(normal((F/H)/G));normal(expand(F/H/G));" }}
