." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "2.  \+
Factoring.  The Maple command  " }{TEXT 275 6 "factor" }{TEXT -1 299 "
 can be used to factor algebraic polynomial expressions and rational e
xpressions.  When rational expressions are factors, any common factors
 are cancelled.  Factor each of the polynomials f, g, h, F, G and H.  \+
Also, factor the algebraic and rational expressions a., b., c., d., e.
, f., g., h. and i." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(f);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 
"6#*(%\"xG\"\"\",&F$F%F%F%F%,&F$F%\"\"#!\"\"F%" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(g);" 
}}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'F'F'F',&*&
